The paper deals with the achievable sum rate of MIMO wireless systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The use of MMSE receivers also suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.SY) and communication systems (cs.COM). Finally, the paper presents new closed-form expressions for the achievable sum rate, which could fall under the category of mathematical modeling (cs.MM).
